  "texts": [
    "Jiang et al. [14] demonstrated that models trained solely on datasets of humanwritten disinformation are less effective at detecting LLMgenerated disinformation.",
    "Moreover, recent works explored the detection of AI-generated disinformation across multiple domains such as Politics, Health, and Science [25], [26].In the real world, the fast iteration of LLMs and their variants makes LLM-generated disinformation detection become more challenging.",
    "In this context, we investigate the novel problem of evolving LLM-generated disinformation detection.",
    "We focus on providing effective methods that are applicable to the constantly evolving nature of LLM-generated disinformation, ensuring robustness against future disinformation.",
    "B. Parameter-Efficient Fine-TuningParameter-efficient fine-tuning (PEFT) has emerged as a significant approach in the adaptation of large pre-trained models to specific tasks while minimizing the computational and storage overhead."
